  "body": "Since we had `Settings` component used in qml only, and since there were a need (and will be more in the future) to access some of locally stored properties from the Nim part, we added `LocalSettingsService` class [here](https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/commit/e0c53b7012354023e367c33093598f7523063aa6). \n\nNow we have two places maintaining the same local file. What we need to do within this ticket is: \n- to expose `LocalSettingsService` to qml part via `SettingsController`\n- to remove all `Settings` components from qml part and update all places accordingly to use exposed controller\n\nBenefits:\n- we will have a single place maintaining locally store files\n- we will get rid of dummy `unknownAccount` file created in `/Status/qt` location since it's a consequence of having `Settings` in qml",
